British Israel Gains Most in Five Months on Melisron Merger Deal

-- B y   D a v i d   W a i n e r
-- 
2011-02-13T10:34:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-13/british-israel-gains-most-in-five-months-on-melisron-merger-deal.html
  British Israel Investments Ltd .
climbed the most since September in Tel Aviv trading as the
investor in malls agreed with  Melisron Ltd . on merger terms.  The shares soared as much as 8.9 percent, the biggest
intraday advance since Sept. 6, to 12.71 shekels. They gained 7
percent to 12.49 shekels as of 12:20 p.m. in Tel Aviv.  British  Israel  and Melisron agreed on the terms of the
acquisition, the companies said today in separate announcements
to the Tel Aviv Stock Exchange. Following additional approvals
for the deal Melisron will bring the acquisition to the
shareholders for a vote, the Kiryat Bialik, Israel-based company
said.  Melisron added 2.7 percent, the most since Feb. 2, to 90.87
shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Wainer in  Tel Aviv  at 
 dwainer1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  